1.  Process kya hota hai aur process table kya hai?
    Process = program jo currently RAM mein run ho raha hai. Jaise Chrome open hai toh ek process hai. 
    Process Table ek registry hai jisme OS saare running processes ka record rakhta hai — unki state, memory, CPU registers sab.
    Interview Tip: One liner: Program = recipe (disk pe), Process = khana bante waqt (RAM mein).

2.  Process ke different states kya hote hain?
    5 states hote hain: New (naya process ban raha hai), Ready (CPU milne ka wait kar raha), Running (CPU use ho raha hai),
    Waiting/Blocked (I/O ka wait kar raha), Terminated (khatam ho gaya). Ek waqt mein sirf ek process Running state mein ho sakta hai.
    Interview Tip: Trick: N-R-R-W-T.

3.  Context Switching kya hota hai?
    Jab CPU ek process se doosre process pe switch karta hai, toh purane process ki state (registers, PC) PCB mein save hoti hai,
    aur naye process ki state load hoti hai. Ye kaam kuch overhead leta hai — isi liye thread switching process switching se fast hoti hai.
    Interview Tip: Sochlo: Paused game ka save = context save. Load = context restore.

4.  PCB (Process Control Block) kya hota hai?
    PCB ek data structure hai jo har process ki puri info rakhta hai — PID, state, program counter, CPU registers, memory info, 
    I/O info, accounting info. Process table = array of PCBs.
    Interview Tip: PCB = process ka Aadhaar card — sari info ek jagah.

5.  Program aur Process mein kya difference hai?
    Program ek static entity hai jo disk pe pada hota hai — instructions ka collection. Process ek dynamic entity hai — 
    wo program jo RAM mein load hokar execute ho raha hai. Ek program se multiple processes ban sakti hain.
    Interview Tip: Program = recipe (stored), Process = khana bante waqt (active).

6.  Zombie process kya hota hai?
    Jab ek child process execution complete kar leta hai lekin parent process abhi uska exit status read nahi kar paya,
    toh wo process zombie hoti hai. Process table mein entry hoti hai lekin actually run nahi hoti.
    Parent jab wait() call karta hai toh entry remove hoti hai.
    Interview Tip: Real analogy: Zombie = employee ne resign kar diya, exit formalities pending hain.

7.  Orphan process kya hota hai?
    Jab parent process child se pehle terminate ho jaata hai, toh child ko orphan kehte hain.
    Linux mein init process (PID 1) aisa orphan processes ko adopt kar leta hai.
    Interview Tip: Yaad rakho: Zombie = child finished, parent busy. Orphan = parent gone, child alive.
